  "body": "### Description\r\nThis issue follows up on #3757 - we have the logic to upgrade Altair states implemented, but not yet integrated into our `StateTransition` processing.  Per the [Altair fork spec](https://github.com/ethereum/eth2.0-specs/blob/v1.1.0-alpha.3/specs/altair/fork.md), the state upgrade should happen in `process_slots`:\r\n> After process_slots of Phase 0 finishes, if state.slot == ALTAIR_FORK_SLOT, an irregular state change is made to upgrade to Altair\r\n\r\n**Note**: Because `process_slots` can run across any number of slots (and therefore fork boundaries), we will likely need to restructure our `StateTransition` logic so that we can hand off processing to the correct spec version as we process through forks.",
